cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AR, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper compares the performance of two wireless networking standards (IEEE 802.11ax and IEEE 802.11ac) in terms of throughput.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the impact of different modulation and coding schemes on the throughput performance.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper may involve the transmission of multimedia data between the two users.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper may involve the evaluation of hardware performance in implementing the two standards.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on security aspects, but it may touch upon the reliability of the channels used for transmission.
